# Code owners for twin-digital/opus.
#
# Takes effect when the `main` ruleset has "Require review from Code Owners" enabled:
# a PR touching an owned path then needs an owning reviewer's approval before merge.
# Agents (the GitHub App) can open PRs and push to branches, but a human owner must
# approve. Solo today — @skleinjung owns everything; the explicit high-risk paths below
# are just documentation of intent (same owner) and future-proofing for a team.

# Default owner for the whole repo
*                       @skleinjung

# Highest blast radius — CI/CD, automation, container, release config.
# Always want an owner's eyes here (esp. workflow changes, which run in CI).
/.github/               @skleinjung
/.github/workflows/     @skleinjung
/.devcontainer/         @skleinjung
/.changeset/            @skleinjung
/.repo-kit.yml          @skleinjung
